# CharacterControlSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Translates held arrow keys into the showcase character's movement and facing animation. Returns early
until InputStateSingletonComponent exists. For each entity tagged CharacterTagComponent it forms a
movement direction from the held arrow keys; while moving it reads the character's current
PositionComponent and emits a CharacterTransformRequestOneFrameComponent setting the new world position
(move speed scaled by the frame delta), and emits a SetSpriteAnimationRequestOneFrameComponent selecting
the animation row for the facing direction with playback on. While idle it emits only a
SetSpriteAnimationRequestOneFrameComponent with playback off and no row change, so the character rests on
its idle frame still facing its last direction. Sole adder of both request types.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read | Held arrow keys; guard (returns early if absent) |
| CharacterTagComponent | read | Marks the arrow-key-controlled character entity |
| PositionComponent | read | The character's current world position (movement origin) |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| CharacterTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | New world position; emitted only on a frame with movement |
| SetSpriteAnimationRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Engine request: facing row (when moving) + playback flag; applied by the engine SpriteAnimationSystem |
